<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6839821>
    dc:description "Fig. 4. Ephydatia muelleri (Lieberkühn, 1856). A. Habitus (P059-170829-4). B. Spiculae, m = megascleres (P059-170830-13), g = gemmuloscleres (P059-130828-18). C. Estimated megasclere size distribution within and between specimens, P059-130829-3 (solid line), P059-170830-13 (dashed) and UP-16-1-2 (dotted). Marks on the x-axis represent spiculae measured. Brackets correspond to ranges in literature (red = Tendal 1967b; blue = Penney & Racek 1968; black = Evans & Montagnes 2019)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/6839821/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

